<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2013-05-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Novel Molecular Type of Clostridium difficile in Neonatal Pigs, Western Australia</TITLE><BODY>Clostridium difficile causes neonatal enteritis in piglets; strains of PCR ribotype 078 are most commonly identified. We investigated C. difficile prevalence in piglets in Australia and isolated a novel strain with a unique pathogenicity locus. In a mouse infection model, this strain produced more weight loss than did a ribotype 078 strain.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>